  "body": "This breaks continious integration usecases. Which is a dealbreaker for orgs/teams doing continous deployment (autodeploy when tests pass).\n\nStandard for mocha runners is to return the number of failing tests. But anything non-zero would be fine.\n\nThis may be caused by `babel-node` executable, so this may be fixed by #80 and/or the changes due to Windows support (#81).\n",
